_source.body: Registering yet another 40-year high, the consumer price index for June came in at 9.1% and solidified at least a 75 basis-point move when the Federal Open Market Committee meets later this month. The Bank of Canada broke the seal on 100 basis points today, and the probability of a similar move by the Federal Reserve spiked after this morning’s inflation report. Whatever the magnitude of its upcoming rate increase, what the Fed has already done will likely put the economy in recession, according to Eric Johnston, and that means earnings are likely to come down. Eric, the head of equity derivatives and cross asset for Cantor Fitzgerald, joins Maggie Lake to talk about why earnings will catalyze the next leg down for equities markets. We also hear from Shawn Hackett about how to trade amid a correction in the commodities market. Want to submit questions? Drop them right here on the Exchange: https://rvtv.io/3ayWL0O. Watch the full Interview...

🤨Hmmm , fear is a powerful tool.. 
The timing is interesting given current state of affairs in the Ukraine..

‘You’ve got this’: New York City releases video about what to do if a nuclear bomb strikes..

The New York mayor has defended the city releasing an information video with step-by-step instructions for what people should do if a nuclear missile strikes...

New York City Mayor Eric Adams has defended the city providing step-by-step instructions for what people should do if the Big Apple is hit with nuclear missiles.

The city’s Emergency Management Department released a 90-second public service announcement on Monday that featured desolate streets and sirens that told New Yorkers what to do in the unlikely event the city was struck by a nuclear weapon, the New York Post reports..
